%N A394975 Array read by ascending antidiagonals: A(n,k) = (1/(n+1)!) * Sum_{j=0..k} (n+k)! * Stirling2(n+j,j) / (k-j)!.
%H A394975 Tomasz Kania, <a href="https://mathoverflow.net/a/509976">Equivalence of pair of integer coefficients</a>, answer to question on MathOverflow, 2026.
%F A394975 A(n, k) = (1/(n+1)!) * Sum_{j=0..min(n, k)} (n+k)! * A340556(n, j) * A143409(k-j, 2*n) / (k-j)! (due to Tomasz Kania).
%F A394975 E.g.f.: (n+1)! * Sum_{k>=0} A(n, k) * x^k / (n+k)! = exp(x) * (Sum_{k=0..n} A340556(n, k) * x^k) / (1-x)^(2*n+1) (due to Tomasz Kania).
%F A394975 From _Peter Luschny_, Apr 09 2026: (Start)
%F A394975 A(n, k) = binomial(n + k, k) * Sum_{j=0..k} (binomial(k, j) * j^(n+j) * (1-j)^(k-j)) / (n + 1).
%F A394975 A(n, k) = A394825(n, k) * binomial(n + k, k) / (n + 1). (End)
%F A394975 A(n, k) = (n+k)*(A(n, k-1) + (k*A(n-1, k) - (n+k-1)*A(n-1, k-1)) / (n+1)) with A(0, k) = k*A(0, k-1) + 1, A(n, 0) = 0^n. - _Mikhail Kurkov_, Apr 16 2026
